title: Independent candidate Fazle Shakoor Khan wins PK-65 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): The Independent candidate Fazle Shakoor Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-65, Charsadda-IV by securing 43,103 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e- Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) candidate Muhammad Ahmed Khan who bagged 18,266 votes.
Voters turnout remained 38 percent.
